import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    median_delay = data['delay'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_delay, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Median Delay: {median_delay:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.boxplot(data['distance'])
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['distance'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    origin_counts = data['origin'].value_counts()
    sns.barplot(x=origin_counts.index, y=origin_counts.values)
    plt.xlabel('Origin Airport')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the most common origin airport?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import seaborn as sns

import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    sns.scatterplot(x='distance', y='delay', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between distance and delay?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data_count = data['date'].value_counts().reset_index()
    data_count.columns = ['date', 'count']
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='count', data=data_count)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flights across different dates?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
